text: I truly believe if you can't train the
way you want to or at least 85% of the
way you want to then pull the plug fix
it and come back to it revisit again
because I've done it I've been the
person who kicks the injury Rock a
little further down the road and pretty
soon I'm only running 15 miles a week
instead of 50 and I get to a race I'm
like I'm not prepared and I have no
confidence where I might have been
better off pulling the plug seeing PT
getting rehab and then putting together
eight decent weeks of workouts and
probably ending up on race day better
